  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Minister's announcement on fuel",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekara said that the unloading of diesel from the two diesel vessels that have arrived in Sri Lanka has been completed.",
        "He also mentioned that another diesel vessel in Colombo port is being unloaded.",
        "He said that a sample for testing has been taken from the 35,000 metric ton oil tanker that has arrived in the country and the landing work will begin tomorrow.",
        "The minister informed that tomorrow (19th) delivery will start by trains and bowsers to the regional depots of the Ceylon Petroleum Storage Terminal.",
        "He also mentioned that the National Youth Brigade and the Ministry of Youth Affairs will help the rural public to register for National Fuel Permits on 21st."
      ],
